canonical:
  title: 延興宮大妃祖母金氏追封和義郡夫人
  author: 閔忠紹
  language: lzh
  text: 敎敍舊勳而錫爵是自古今擧懿族以疏封勿論存歿行之久矣續莫厚焉延興宮大妃祖母金氏積慶居多傳芳不歇曾修峻德及後嗣以克明果有令孫輔先君而益盛可謂源深而流遠豈無自葉以霑根宜覃出綍之恩用示漏泉之澤今追封和義郡夫人
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 延興宮大妃祖母金氏追封和義郡夫人
  author: 閔忠紹
  language: lzh
  text: 敎。敍舊勳而錫爵。是自古今。擧懿族以疏封。勿論存歿。行之久矣。續莫厚焉。延興宮大妃祖母金氏。積慶居多。傳芳不歇。曾修峻德。及後嗣以克明。果有令孫。輔先君而益盛。可謂源深而流遠。豈無自葉以霑根。宜覃出綍之恩。用示漏泉之澤。今追封和義郡夫人。
korean:
  title: 연흥궁 대비 조모 김씨 추봉 화의군부인
  author: 민충소
  language: kor
  text: 교하노라. 옛 공을 생각하여 관작을 내리는 것은 고금(古今)이 한 가지요, 의족(懿族)을 들어서 분봉(分封)하는 것은 생사(生死)를 논하지 않는 것이다. 시행한 지 오래이니 계속하는 것보다 더 후한 일은 없다.연흥궁(延興宮) 대비(大妃)의 조모 김씨는 경사를 쌓은 것이 매우 많았고, 남겨 놓은 아름다운 일이 아직도 다하지 않았다. 일찍이 큰 덕을 닦아 놓아 후사에까지 능히 그 덕을 밝혔고, 과연 어진 손자를 두어 선군(先君)을 도와서 더욱 거룩하게 하였다. 근원이 깊으면 흐름도 영원한 법인데, 어찌 잎사귀로부터 뿌리를 적시는 일이 없겠는가. 관직을 제수하는 은전을 베풀어서, 누천(漏泉)의 혜택을 보이는 것이 마땅하기에, 이제 화의군부인(和義郡夫人)을 추봉(追封)한다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0280_010_0110&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Edict Granting Posthumous Title of Lady of Hwaui County to the Grandmother of the Crown Princess of Yeonheung Palace
  author: Min Chung-so
  language: eng
  text: |-
    An edict is hereby proclaimed. To honor past merit and bestow ranks is the way of all ages, both ancient and modern. To select virtuous families for enfeoffment knows no distinction between the living and the deceased. This practice has long been observed, and none surpasses its generosity in continuation.

    The grandmother, Lady Kim, of the Crown Princess of Yeonheung Palace accumulated abundant blessings and left behind fragrant virtue that has not yet faded. She cultivated great virtue in her time, and this illuminated the hearts of her descendants. She indeed bore a worthy grandson who aided the former sovereign and thereby enhanced his glory. When the source runs deep, so flows the stream eternal—how could the leaves not moisten the roots from which they spring? Thus do we extend the grace of official bestowal to manifest the blessing that flows like water through a leaking vessel.

    We hereby grant posthumous ennoblement as Lady of Hwaui County.
  footnotes:
    - Yeonheung Palace (延興宮) was a residence for the mother or grandmother of a reigning monarch in Korean court tradition.
    - The metaphor of 'root and branch' (근원과 흐름) reflects Confucian family values, suggesting that virtue flows through generations.
    - The 'leaking vessel' (누천) imagery represents the flowing and spreading of imperial grace to all levels of society.
